{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775830404707,"sessionID":"ses_288449b0fffeJgiIX2CKGY9yx3","part":{"id":"prt_d77bb85f3001GSimjlAGQHB3Pv","messageID":"msg_d77bb71620018lOp540Ws45ihO","sessionID":"ses_288449b0fffeJgiIX2CKGY9yx3","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_725e1b77d667409a9be01d80","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project structure","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project structure thoroughly. I need to understand:\n\n1. The overall project structure - what directories exist at the root level\n2. The pkg/router module - what files exist, what they do, current authentication mechanisms\n3. Any existing JWT-related code in the project\n4. Any existing authentication/authorization patterns in the codebase\n5. Configuration files and how the project is structured\n\nSearch in the directory: /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z\n\nLook for:\n- pkg/router/ directory contents\n- Any auth, jwt, token related files\n- go.mod to understand dependencies\n- Any existing middleware patterns\n- Configuration or spec files related to authentication\n\nReturn a comprehensive summary of:\n1. Project structure overview\n2. pkg/router module details (all files and their purposes)\n3. Current authentication mechanisms (if any)\n4. Related dependencies in go.mod\n5. Any existing JWT or token handling code\n6. Middleware patterns used","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_2884461f7ffeSROM7wwUIPjZyg (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nI now have a thorough understanding of the entire project. Here is my comprehensive summary:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Project Analysis: AgentCube\n\n### 1. Project Structure Overview\n\nThe project is **AgentCube** (`github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`), a Kubernetes-native agent runtime and sandbox orchestration system written in Go (Go 1.25.0).\n\n**Root-level directories:**\n\n| Directory | Purpose |\n|-----------|---------|\n| `pkg/` | Core Go packages (router, store, apis, workloadmanager, common) |\n| `client-go/` | Generated Kubernetes typed clientset and informers |\n| `changes/` | Change requests (AR-001 through AR-011) with design/spec/tasks |\n| `ci-cd/` | CI/CD design and spec |\n| `cli-toolkit/` | CLI tool design and spec |\n| `code-execution/` | PicoD code execution engine design and spec |\n| `deployment/` | Deployment design, spec, and client-go docs |\n| `idle-cleanup/` | Idle session cleanup design and spec |\n| `integrations/` | Integration design and spec |\n| `python-sdk/` | Python SDK design and spec |\n| `sandbox-orchestration/` | Sandbox orchestration design and spec |\n| `session-routing/` | Session routing design and spec |\n| `session-store/` | Session store design and spec |\n| `testing/` | TDD manifest defining required test coverage |\n\n**Key root files:**\n- `go.mod` / `go.sum` -- Go module definition\n- `design.md` -- AR-009 Router design document\n- `delta-spec.md` -- Formal specification for the router module\n- `proposal.md` -- High-level project proposal\n- `project.md` -- Project overview\n- `test_spec.md` -- Test specifications\n\n---\n\n### 2. pkg/router Module Details (12 files)\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/config.go` | Configuration struct (`Config`) with defaults: port 8080, max 1000 concurrent requests, session timeouts |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/server.go` | Main `Server` struct, constructor `NewServer`, route registration, HTTP/h2c server start/shutdown with graceful signal handling |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/router.go` | Generic `Router` interface with `AddRoute`/`RemoveRoute`/`ServeHTTP`, backed by `routerImpl` with mutex-protected route map |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/proxy.go` | Reverse proxy logic: `handleInvoke`, `handleAgentInvoke`, `handleCodeInterpreterInvoke`, `forwardToSandbox` with `httputil.ReverseProxy`, Director, ModifyResponse, ErrorHandler |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/jwt.go` | **JWTManager**: RSA-2048 key generation, RS256 token signing, K8s Secret persistence (`picod-router-identity`), ephemeral key fallback outside cluster |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/middleware.go` | Three middleware functions: `ConcurrencyLimitMiddleware` (semaphore-based 429), `RequestLoggerMiddleware` (structured slog), `TraceIDMiddleware` (UUID-based X-Trace-Id) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/session_manager.go` | `SessionManager` interface + `manager` impl: session lookup/creation via store, sandbox creation via WorkloadManager HTTP calls, K8s service account token attachment |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/backend.go` | `Backend` struct with health tracking, `BackendHealthChecker` with configurable thresholds and default `/health` endpoint checker |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/loadbalancer.go` | `LoadBalancer` interface with two implementations: `RoundRobinBalancer` and `LeastConnectionsBalancer` (atomic counters) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/informer.go` | `InformerManager`: K8s SharedInformerFactory watching AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs with event handlers (currently stub logging) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/health.go` | Health endpoints: `/health/live` (always 200) and `/health/ready` (checks session manager) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/errors.go` | Custom error types: `SessionNotFoundError`, `SandboxTemplateNotFoundError`, `SessionTerminatedError` |\n\n**Registered routes (from server.go):**\n- `GET /health/live` -- no middleware\n- `GET /health/ready` -- no middleware\n- `/v1` group with `gin.Logger()`, `gin.Recovery()`, `ConcurrencyLimitMiddleware`:\n  - `GET/POST /v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path`\n  - `GET/POST /v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path`\n\n---\n\n### 3. Current Authentication Mechanisms\n\nThe project has **two distinct authentication patterns**:\n\n#### A. Router JWT Signing (OUTBOUND -- token generation, no verification)\n\nLocation: `pkg/router/jwt.go` and `pkg/router/proxy.go`\n\n- The router **generates and signs** JWTs using RS256 with a 2048-bit RSA key pair\n- Keys are persisted to a K8s Secret named `picod-router-identity` in namespace from `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` env var (default: `default`)\n- JWT claims: `exp` (now + 5 minutes), `iat` (now), `iss` (\"agentcube-router\"), plus custom claims like `session_id`\n- JWTs are **injected as outbound `Authorization: Bearer <token>`** headers when proxying to `Sandbox` or `SandboxClaim` kind endpoints\n- **The router does NOT verify incoming JWTs** -- there is no AuthMiddleware on the router's own routes\n- If not running in-cluster, ephemeral keys are used (warning logged, no error)\n\n#### B. PicoD JWT Verification (INBOUND -- token validation)\n\nLocation: Documented in `code-execution/design.md` (reference implementation from `/tmp/agentcube-ref`)\n\n- PicoD (code execution sidecar) has a full `AuthManager` with `AuthMiddleware`\n- Loads RSA public key from `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` env var (PEM-encoded PKIX)\n- **Fatal if key is missing** -- server will not start without it\n- Middleware validates incoming `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header\n- Uses `jwt.Parse()` with `WithExpirationRequired()`, `WithIssuedAt()`, `WithLeeway(1 minute)`\n- Requires `*jwt.SigningMethodRSA` type (rejects HMAC methods like HS256)\n- On success, wraps request body with `http.MaxBytesReader` (32 MiB limit)\n- Returns 401 with `{\"error\": string, \"code\": int, \"detail\": string}` on failure\n\n#### C. WorkloadManager Bearer Token Extraction\n\nLocation: `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox_create.go`\n\n- Extracts Bearer token from `Authorization` header\n- Uses token to create per-user K8s dynamic clients (via `TokenCache` or `UserClientFactory`)\n- Controlled by `EnableAuth` flag on handler\n\n#### D. Session Manager K8s Service Account Token\n\nLocation: `pkg/router/session_manager.go` (line 133-136)\n\n- Reads `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`\n- Attaches as `Authorization: Bearer <token>` when calling WorkloadManager API\n\n---\n\n### 4. Related Dependencies in go.mod\n\n**Direct dependencies relevant to auth/routing:**\n\n| Dependency | Version | Usage |\n|-----------|---------|-------|\n| `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | v1.10.0 | HTTP routing engine, middleware framework |\n| `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | v5.2.1 | RS256 JWT signing (router) and verification (PicoD) |\n| `github.com/google/uuid` | v1.6.0 | Trace ID generation in middleware |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | v0.34.1 | K8s API access, Secret management, Informers |\n| `k8s.io/api` | v0.34.1 | K8s API types |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | v0.34.1 | K8s errors, schema, runtime |\n| `golang.org/x/net` | v0.51.0 | HTTP/2 and h2c support |\n| `golang.org/x/oauth2` | v0.27.0 (indirect) | OAuth2 support |\n| `golang.org/x/crypto` | v0.48.0 (indirect) | Cryptographic primitives |\n\n---\n\n### 5. Existing JWT / Token Handling Code\n\n**`pkg/router/jwt.go` -- JWTManager (129 lines)**\n\nConstants:\n- `rsaKeySize = 2048`\n- `jwtExpiration = 5 * time.Minute`\n- `IdentitySecretName = \"picod-router-identity\"`\n- `PrivateKeyDataKey = \"private.pem\"`\n- `PublicKeyDataKey = \"public.pem\"`\n- `IdentityNamespace` -- variable, set from `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` env var (default: `\"default\"`)\n\nStruct:\n```go\ntype JWTManager struct {\n    privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey\n    publicKey  *rsa.PublicKey\n    clientset  kubernetes.Interface\n}\n```\n\nMethods:\n- `NewJWTManager()` -- generates RSA-2048 key pair in memory\n- `GenerateToken(claims map[string]interface{}) (string, error)` -- creates JWT with base claims (exp, iat, iss=\"agentcube-router\") + custom claims, signs with RS256\n- `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx)` -- creates K8s Secret with key pair, or loads existing key pair from Secret; falls back to ephemeral keys if not in-cluster\n- `loadPrivateKeyPEM(data []byte)` -- parses PKCS1 PEM-encoded private key\n\n**`pkg/router/proxy.go` -- JWT Injection (lines 148-163)**\n\n```go\nif kind == types.SandboxKind || kind == types.SandboxClaimKind {\n    if s.jwtManager != nil {\n        token, err := s.jwtManager.GenerateToken(map[string]interface{}{\n            \"session_id\": sessionID,\n        })\n        // on error: return 500 {\"code\":\"JWT_SIGNING_FAILED\",\"error\":\"failed to sign request\"}\n        req.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+token)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key gap:** There is no JWT verification middleware on the router itself. The router signs tokens for downstream services but does not validate incoming tokens. The TDD manifest (`testing/agentcube_tdd_manifest.md`) explicitly calls for an `AuthMiddleware` with tests for invalid/expired JWTs returning 401, and AR-011 (\"Router JWT Authentication and Signing\") is the planned change request to add this -- but its design.md, proposal.md, and tasks.md are all TODO placeholders.\n\n---\n\n### 6. Middleware Patterns Used\n\n**Current middleware in `pkg/router/middleware.go`:**\n\n1. **`ConcurrencyLimitMiddleware(maxConcurrent int) gin.HandlerFunc`**\n   - Buffered channel semaphore pattern\n   - Returns 429 `{\"error\":\"server overloaded, please try again later\",\"code\":\"SERVER_OVERLOADED\"}` when exhausted\n   - Applied to `/v1` route group only\n\n2. **`RequestLoggerMiddleware() gin.HandlerFunc`**\n   - Structured logging via `slog.Info`\n   - Logs: method, path, status, duration_ms, trace_id\n\n3. **`TraceIDMiddleware() gin.HandlerFunc`**\n   - Generates UUID, sets `X-Trace-Id` on both request and response headers\n\n4. **`FormatDuration(ms int64) string`** -- utility function\n\n**Gin built-in middleware used:**\n- `gin.Logger()` -- on `/v1` group\n- `gin.Recovery()` -- on `/v1` group\n\n**Middleware registration pattern (server.go):**\n```go\nv1 := s.engine.Group(\"/v1\")\nv1.Use(gin.Logger())\nv1.Use(gin.Recovery())\nv1.Use(ConcurrencyLimitMiddleware(s.config.MaxConcurrentRequests))\n```\n\n**Reference pattern from PicoD (code-execution/design.md):**\n```go\napi := engine.Group(\"/api\")\napi.Use(s.authManager.AuthMiddleware())\n```\n\nThis shows the established pattern: create a Gin group, apply middleware via `.Use()`, then register routes within the group.\n\n---\n\n### Summary of Key Findings\n\n1. **The router currently ONLY signs JWTs (outbound); it does NOT verify them (inbound).** There is no authentication middleware protecting the router's own endpoints.\n\n2. **AR-011** is the planned change request to add \"Router JWT Authentication and Signing\" but all its documentation files are empty TODOs.\n\n3. **The TDD manifest requires `AuthMiddleware` tests** (Test-RT-1: invalid JWT returns 401, Test-RT-2: expired JWT returns \"Token Expired\"), indicating this is expected but not yet implemented.\n\n4. **The PicoD component already has a complete JWT verification pattern** (`AuthManager` with `AuthMiddleware`) that could serve as a reference implementation for the router.\n\n5. **The JWT key pair is shared between Router and PicoD** via the K8s Secret `picod-router-identity` -- the router stores both keys, and the workloadmanager injects the public key into PicoD pods as `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` env var.\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_2884461f7ffeSROM7wwUIPjZyg","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775830277636,"end":1775830404705}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775830404755,"sessionID":"ses_288449b0fffeJgiIX2CKGY9yx3","part":{"id":"prt_d77bd8e62001zlKEa7Q7NECqQM","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d77bb71620018lOp540Ws45ihO","sessionID":"ses_288449b0fffeJgiIX2CKGY9yx3","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":19679,"input":19227,"output":292,"reasoning":160,"cache":{"write":0,"read":0}},"cost":0.006052904}}
